---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/ui/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { buildBreadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/seo';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Legal', url: '/legal/' },
  { name: 'Cookie Policy', url: '/legal/cookies/' },
];

const lastUpdated = '2026-05-22';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy"
  description="Full breakdown of every cookie Calctube uses, why we use it, who provides it, and how to opt out. GDPR + AdSense compliant."
  schemas={[buildBreadcrumbSchema(breadcrumbs)]}
>
  <article class="container-prose py-8">
    <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbs} />
    <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <h2>What are cookies?</h2>
    <p>
      Cookies are small text files stored on your device by your browser when you visit a website. Some cookies are essential — without them, parts of the site stop working. Others are used for analytics or advertising. This page lists every cookie we use, why we use it, and how you can control them.
    </p>

    <h2>Your control: Consent Mode v2</h2>
    <p>
      On your first visit, Calctube shows a cookie banner with two clear choices:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Accept all</strong> — analytics and advertising cookies are enabled. We see anonymized traffic patterns and (once AdSense is approved) you may see relevant ads.</li>
      <li><strong>Essential only</strong> — only strictly-necessary cookies are set. No analytics, no ads. The calculators still work perfectly.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We use <a href="https://developers.google.com/tag-platform/security/concepts/consent-mode" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Consent Mode v2</a> with default-deny: until you explicitly accept, Google Analytics and (future) Google AdSense run in <em>consent-denied</em> mode, meaning no personal identifiers are stored and no personalization happens. Your choice is remembered for 365 days in a single cookie (<code>calctube-consent</code>) so the banner doesn't reappear every visit.
    </p>
    <p>
      To change your choice later: clear your browser cookies for <code>calctube.com</code> and the banner will reappear on next visit.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies we use</h2>

    <h3>Strictly necessary</h3>
    <table class="w-full text-sm border border-slate-200 my-4">
      <thead class="bg-slate-100">
        <tr>
          <th class="text-left p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Cookie</th>
          <th class="text-left p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Purpose</th>
          <th class="text-left p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Provider</th>
          <th class="text-left p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Duration</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200"><code>calctube-consent</code></td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Stores your cookie banner choice (all / essential-only)</td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Calctube (first-party)</td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">365 days</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="p-2"><code>__cf_bm</code>, <code>cf_clearance</code></td>
          <td class="p-2">Bot protection and DDoS mitigation by Cloudflare</td>
          <td class="p-2">Cloudflare</td>
          <td class="p-2">Session / 30 min</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
      <strong>Essential cookies are always set</strong> regardless of your banner choice — they make the site work and protect it from abuse. They contain no personal identifiers.
    </p>

    <h3>Analytics (only set after you accept)</h3>
    <table class="w-full text-sm border border-slate-200 my-4">
      <thead class="bg-slate-100">
        <tr>
          <th class="text-left p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Cookie</th>
          <th class="text-left p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Purpose</th>
          <th class="text-left p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Provider</th>
          <th class="text-left p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Duration</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200"><code>_ga</code></td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Distinguishes unique users (Google Analytics 4)</td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Google Analytics (third-party)</td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">2 years</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200"><code>_ga_PVB5YV8KFP</code></td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Per-property GA4 session state for Calctube</td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Google Analytics</td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">2 years</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="p-2"><code>_gid</code></td>
          <td class="p-2">Distinguishes users for 24-hour windows</td>
          <td class="p-2">Google Analytics</td>
          <td class="p-2">24 hours</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Advertising (only set after you accept, once AdSense is live)</h3>
    <table class="w-full text-sm border border-slate-200 my-4">
      <thead class="bg-slate-100">
        <tr>
          <th class="text-left p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Cookie</th>
          <th class="text-left p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Purpose</th>
          <th class="text-left p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Provider</th>
          <th class="text-left p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Duration</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200"><code>__gads</code>, <code>__gpi</code></td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Ad frequency capping and personalization for Google AdSense</td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Google AdSense</td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">13 months</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200"><code>IDE</code>, <code>NID</code></td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Cross-site ad measurement by DoubleClick / Google</td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">Google (third-party)</td>
          <td class="p-2 border-b border-slate-200">13–24 months</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="p-2"><code>FPID</code>, <code>FPLC</code></td>
          <td class="p-2">First-party identifiers (only if you accept Google personalized ads)</td>
          <td class="p-2">Google AdSense</td>
          <td class="p-2">13 months</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
      AdSense is currently not enabled on Calctube — the table above documents what <em>will</em> be set once we go live with ads, so this policy stays accurate.
    </p>

    <h3>Local storage (not a cookie, but worth knowing)</h3>
    <p>
      A few calculators (mortgage, EMI, SIP) save your last-used inputs in your browser's <code>localStorage</code> so you don't have to re-enter them on your next visit. This data <strong>never leaves your device</strong> — it isn't sent to any server. Clearing your browser data removes it.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party services and where to opt out</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — opt out browser-wide with the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Google Analytics Opt-out Add-on</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Google personalized ads</strong> — manage at <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Google Ads Settings</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Cloudflare cookies</strong> — see <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/cookie-policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Cloudflare's cookie policy</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Industry-wide opt-out</strong> for behavioral ads: <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.eu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">YourOnlineChoices.eu</a> (EU), <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">DAA WebChoices</a> (US).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Do Not Track</h2>
    <p>
      Calctube respects the legal-safe default: until you actively click "Accept all", we treat your visit as if Do Not Track were on. Analytics still receives an anonymized pageview-only signal so we can roughly count traffic, but no identifiers persist and no behavioral profile is built.
    </p>

    <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Calctube is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided data through our site, email <a href="mailto:privacy@calctube.com">privacy@calctube.com</a> and we will delete it.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We update this page whenever we add or remove a cookie. Material changes (new third-party providers, new ad partners) trigger the consent banner to reappear so you can re-choose.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Cookie questions, complaints, or data subject requests: <a href="mailto:privacy@calctube.com">privacy@calctube.com</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
